HEADWORD: Caducity
<hw>Ca*du"ci*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>caducitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>caducit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Caducous</er>.]</ety> <def>Tendency to fall; the feebleness of old
age; senility.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[A] jumble of youth and <qex>caducity</qex>.</q>
